  "market_context": "Bearish bias confirmed on 15-min with protected swing and retracement. Analyst drops to 3-min to evaluate continuation entry after candle 2 expansion that did not sweep short-term liquidity.",
  "key_observation": "Candle 2 expanded but left short-term liquidity (a prior high) intact, making a continuation trade in candle 3 viable with defined stop above the un-swept high and target at prior low.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a protected swing on the 15-minute chart where price closed below a prior level after reaching fair value gaps, establishing bearish bias.",
    "Step 2: Dropped to the 3-minute chart and noted an existing order block formed *before* the open of the new higher-time-frame candle, allowing anticipation of lower price action.",
    "Step 3: Observed that candle 2 expanded but did *not* take out the short-term high (liquidity remained intact), making it a 'less-than-ideal' but still tradable continuation setup.",
    "Step 4: Set stop loss just above the un-swept short-term high and target at the prior low to achieve ~1:2 risk-reward, using the pre-formed order block as the entry zone.",
    "Step 5: Confirmed candle 3 formed a protected swing by taking out the short-term high and closing below it, validating the continuation lower."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price expanded lower after candle 3, confirming the continuation trade; analyst noted it took time but executed as anticipated.",
  "lessons": "A less-than-ideal candle 2 can still yield high-probability continuation entries if short-term liquidity remains un-swept—this preserves a clear target and stop placement zone aligned with PD arrays and structure.",
